  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1023600,
    "dDurationMs": 3490,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "To close things off here I have with me Lisha Li who did her PhD work on the"
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1027090,
    "dDurationMs": 3627,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "theoretical side of deep learning and who currently works at a venture capital"
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1030717,
    "dDurationMs": 3903,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "firm called Amplify Partners who kindly provided some of the funding for this video."
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1035460,
    "dDurationMs": 3660,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "So Lisha one thing I think we should quickly bring up is this sigmoid function."
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1039700,
    "dDurationMs": 3458,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "As I understand it early networks use this to squish the relevant weighted"
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1043158,
    "dDurationMs": 3364,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "sum into that interval between zero and one, you know kind of motivated"
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1046522,
    "dDurationMs": 3318,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "by this biological analogy of neurons either being inactive or active."
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1050280,
    "dDurationMs": 3760,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "Exactly.\nBut relatively few modern networks actually use sigmoid anymore."
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1054320,
    "dDurationMs": 1440,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "Yeah.\nIt's kind of old school right?"
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1055760,
    "dDurationMs": 3220,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "Yeah or rather ReLU seems to be much easier to train."
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1059400,
    "dDurationMs": 2940,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "And ReLU, ReLU stands for rectified linear unit?"
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1062680,
    "dDurationMs": 4721,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "Yes it's this kind of function where you're just taking a max of zero"
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1067401,
    "dDurationMs": 4653,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "and a where a is given by what you were explaining in the video and"
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1072054,
    "dDurationMs": 4516,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "what this was sort of motivated from I think was a partially by a"
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1076570,
    "dDurationMs": 4790,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "biological analogy with how neurons would either be activated or not."
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1081360,
    "dDurationMs": 4660,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "And so if it passes a certain threshold it would be the identity function but if it did"
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1086020,
    "dDurationMs": 4820,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "not then it would just not be activated so it'd be zero so it's kind of a simplification."
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1091160,
    "dDurationMs": 4535,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "Using sigmoids didn't help training or it was very difficult to"
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1095695,
    "dDurationMs": 4534,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "train at some point and people just tried ReLU and it happened"
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1100229,
    "dDurationMs": 4391,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "to work very well for these incredibly deep neural networks."
    } ]
  }, {
    "tStartMs": 1105100,
    "dDurationMs": 540,
    "segs": [ {
      "utf8": "All right thank you Lisha."
